From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000072 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gemini Mainline Maintainers <gemini-mainline@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 10:20:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] spi: mediatek: add MT6797 compatible alias

The MT6797 vendor controller uses the legacy SPI register block with
16-bit chip-select and clock timing fields, pad selection, mandatory TX
dummy data, and extended DMA addressing.  These properties match the
existing spi-mt65xx mt6765_compat profile.

Add the MT6797 compatible to the binding and select that profile in the
driver.  Board nodes remain disabled until their pinctrl, clocks, and a
safe runtime transfer are validated.

---
 Documentation/devicetree/bindings/spi/mediatek,spi-mt65xx.yaml | 1 +
 drivers/spi/spi-mt65xx.c                                      | 2 ++
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/spi/mediatek,spi-mt65xx.yaml b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/spi/mediatek,spi-mt65xx.yaml
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/spi/mediatek,spi-mt65xx.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/spi/mediatek,spi-mt65xx.yaml
@@ -27,6 +27,7 @@ properties:
       - items:
           - enum:
               - mediatek,mt6779-spi
+              - mediatek,mt6797-spi
               - mediatek,mt8186-spi
               - mediatek,mt8192-spi
               - mediatek,mt8195-spi
diff --git a/drivers/spi/spi-mt65xx.c b/drivers/spi/spi-mt65xx.c
--- a/drivers/spi/spi-mt65xx.c
+++ b/drivers/spi/spi-mt65xx.c
@@ -251,7 +251,10 @@ static const struct of_device_id mtk_spi_of_match[] = {
 	},
 	{ .compatible = "mediatek,mt6765-spi",
 		.data = (void *)&mt6765_compat,
 	},
+	{ .compatible = "mediatek,mt6797-spi",
+		.data = (void *)&mt6765_compat,
+	},
 	{ .compatible = "mediatek,mt6991-spi",
 		.data = (void *)&mt6991_compat,
 	},
-- 
